  <static seed="98" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionMultiplicationWordProblems20.pg">
    <statement><p>A town has <m>300</m> residents in total, of which <m>{{\frac{5}{6}}}</m> are Latino Americans.
How many Latino Americans reside in this town?</p>
<p>There are <fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/> Latino Americans residing in this town.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>250</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>When we use the word <lq/>of<rq/> in expressions like <lq/><m>{{\frac{5}{6}}}</m> of <m>300</m>,<rq/> we can translate <lq/>of<rq/> into the multiplication symbol.</p>
<p>In this problem, to find <m>{{\frac{5}{6}}}</m> of <m>300</m>, we compute:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{5}{6}}} \cdot 300 
      \amp = {{\frac{5}{6}}} \cdot \frac{300}{1}  \\
      \amp = \frac{5}{1} \cdot \frac{50}{1}  \\
      \amp = \frac{{250}}{1} \\
      \amp = {250}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>There are <m>{250}</m> Latino Americans residing in this town.</p>
</solution>
